<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="101" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,518,1408]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,914,940]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet kolriana is derived from the name of Korean Lichen Research Institute (KoLRI), the first place devoted to lichenological work in 
<collectingCountry box="[791,935,950,976]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">South Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,518,1408]" box="[189,976,985,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,491,985,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">Habitat and distribution:</emphasis>
—Found on rock surfaces at mid elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="101" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,518,1408]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,308,1022,1048]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">Remarks:</emphasis>
—This new species is characterized by the yellowish green upper surface, the adnate to loosely adnate thallus, the black lower surface, the presence simple to branched, subglobose to cylindrical isidia and by the presence of atranorin and salazinic acid as major components in the cortex and medulla respectively, together with cortical usnic acid. Unfortunately, we failed to obtain ITS sequences for this new taxon so its phylogenetic relationships remain unclear.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,518,1408]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kurok.) Elix (2003 b: 400)" authorityName="Elix" authorityPageNumber="400" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Kurok." box="[515,947,1202,1229]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Xanthoparmelia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="murina">
<emphasis box="[515,629,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">X. murina</emphasis>
(Kurok.) 
<bibRefCitation author="Elix, J. A." box="[744,947,1202,1228]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101" pagination="395 - 403" refId="ref8996" refString="Elix, J. A. (2003 b) The lichen genus Paraparmelia, a synonym of Xanthoparmelia (Ascomycota, Parmeliaceae). Mycotaxon 87: 395 - 403." type="journal article" year="2003">Elix (2003b: 400)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of adnate to loosely adnate thallus, sublinear to subirregular lobes, black lower surface and the presence salazinic acid and atranorin. However, it is differentiated by dull yellowish green thallus, the presence of isidia with constricted base and usnic acid in the upper cortex. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Elix &amp; J. Johnst.) Elix (2003 b: 398)" authorityName="Elix" authorityPageNumber="398" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Elix &amp; J. Johnst." box="[219,809,1310,1337]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Xanthoparmelia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="atrocapnodes">
<emphasis box="[219,400,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">X. atrocapnodes</emphasis>
(Elix &amp; J. Johnst.) 
<bibRefCitation author="Elix, J. A." box="[612,809,1310,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101" pagination="395 - 403" refId="ref8996" refString="Elix, J. A. (2003 b) The lichen genus Paraparmelia, a synonym of Xanthoparmelia (Ascomycota, Parmeliaceae). Mycotaxon 87: 395 - 403." type="journal article" year="2003">Elix (2003b: 398)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is another related species, but it contains norstictic acid as major compounds and lacks usnic acid. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Maheu &amp; A. Gillet) Hale (1974: 489)" authorityName="Hale" authorityPageNumber="489" authorityYear="1974" baseAuthorityName="Maheu &amp; A. Gillet" box="[577,1122,1346,1373]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Xanthoparmelia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tinctina">
<emphasis box="[577,693,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">X. tinctina</emphasis>
(Maheu &amp; A. Gillet) 
<bibRefCitation author="Hale, M. E." box="[930,1122,1346,1372]" pageId="5" pageNumber="101" pagination="479 - 490" refId="ref9419" refString="Hale, M. E. (1974) Bulbothrix, Parmelina, Relicina, and Xanthoparmelia, four new genera in the Parmeliaceae. Phytologia 28: 479 - 490." type="journal article" year="1974">Hale (1974: 489)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jayalal, Divakar &amp; Hur" authorityYear="2014" box="[1319,1444,1346,1372]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Xanthoparmelia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kolriana">
<emphasis box="[1319,1444,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="101">X. kolriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but lacks atranorin and chloroatranorin.
</paragraph>
